WorldStage Newsonline–  Stanbic IBTC Holdings Plc, MRS Oil , Neimeth International Pharmaceuticals Plc, Sterling Bank Plc, McNichols Consolidated, Courteville Business Solutions Plc, and Ardova Plc have joined other to host their Board of Directors meetings to consider their third quarter 2020 results. Stanbic IBTC Holdings PLC Stanbic IBTC Holdings PLC has notified the NSE and our Shareholders, that a meeting of its Board of Directors is scheduled to hold on Friday 23 October 2020 at 10:00am. The meeting will discuss amongst other items, the Company’s Unaudited Financial Statements for the third quarter 30 September 2020. The closed period for the release of the 3rd quarter results is from Thursday 15 October 2020 until the release of the Company’s third quarter unaudited financial statements. MRS Oil MRS Oil Nigeria Plc said a meeting of its Board of Directors will hold on Wednesday, October 28, 2020 at 10:30am, to deliberate on the 2020, 3rd Quarter Unaudited Results (Q3 UFS 2020), amongst other things. Closed period is  from Tuesday, October 13, 2020 till twenty-four (24) hours after filing the Q3 UFS 2020 at The Exchange. Neimeth Neimeth International Pharmaceuticals Plc to hold its board meeting on  29th October 2020 to consider its Q4 and full year result ended 30th September 2020. The closed period is from 14th October, 2020. Sterling Bank Sterling Bank Plc has notified the Nigerian Stock Exchange  and its shareholders that its board meeting will be held in Lagos on Thursday, 29th October, 2020 at 10.00am to consider the Bank’s Unaudited Financial Statements for the period ended 30th September, 2020. The Bank had declared a closed period for trading in its shares from 14th October, 2020 until 24 hours after the Unaudited Financial Statements for the period ended 30th September, 2020 are released on the floor of The Exchange. McNichols Consolidated McNichols Consolidated Plc said its board meeting will hold on 28th October 2020 to approve the Q3 2020 result while the closed period will start from 12th October. Courteville Business Solutions Courteville Business Solutions Plc said the meeting of its Board of Directors is scheduled to hold on Thursday October 29, 2020 to consider among other things, the unaudited Financial Statements for the period ended 30 th September, 2020. The Company will commence a Closed Period for trading in the Company’s shares from Wednesday, October 14, 2020 until 24 hours after the unaudited Financial Statements for the period ended 30th September, 2020 is released to the public. Ardova PLC Ardova Plc has notified the Exchange and investing public that the meeting of its Board of Directors has been scheduled to hold on Thursday, October 29, 2020 to consider and approve the Unaudited Financial Statement for the period ended 30th September 2020, amongst other things. The closed period shall commence on Wednesday October 14, 2020. Ellah Lakes Plc A meeting of the Board of Directors of Ellah Lakes Plc  will hold on Thursday, 29 October 2020 at 5th floor, AIICO Plaza, Plot PC 12, Churchgate Street, Victoria Island, Lagos at 11.00 am, according t the company. It said the meeting is to consider, among other matters, the approval of the Audited Accounts of the Company for the year ended 31 July 2020, the 1st Quarter Unaudited Accounts and the date of the Company’s Annual General Meeting. Closed Period for the Company which will commence from Wednesday 14 October 2020 until 24 (twenty-four) hours after the Financials are released to the public. The Initiates Plc The Initiates Plc said that the 36th Meeting of its Board of Directors shall be held virtual on Friday, the 30th day of October, 2020 by 10:00am to consider among other things: the Company’s Strategic Plan Committee report; audit Committee Report & Adoption/approval of the Quarter 3 Management Account; the Management’s Report; the Compensation/Corporate Governance report The commencement of a closed period for trading in its shares from 15th October, 2020 until 24 hours after the outcome of the Board meeting have been announced to the Market.